Loup Ventures analyst Gene Munster said Thursday that Apple (NASDAQ:AAPL) could catch up to Elon Musk's Tesla (NASDAQ:TSLA) in the creation of an autonomous car by leveraging its expertise in AI and hardware. 
 
"When you stack Apple up against Tesla they are probably closer than you think to where Tesla's at today," he told CNBC. 
 
 
 
Munster said the latest reports come from a dependable reporter with a long track record of correctly tracking Apple's moves and the reports have beyond the typical chatter that often surrounds the iPhone maker.
